---

---

<section id="story" class="py-24 px-6 max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <div class="mb-16 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
            Why We Built <span class="text-orange-500">Vayload</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            From frustration with bloated systems to a lean, extensible solution for everyone.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-20">
        <div class="space-y-6">
            <div
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 mb-4 text-orange-400 font-bold tracking-widest text-xs uppercase"
            >
                <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    width="14"
                    height="14"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                >
                    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
                    <line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="12"></line>
                    <line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12.01" y2="8"></line>
                </svg>
                The Problem
            </div>

            <p class="text-lg text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
                For years, we worked with WordPress creating plugins. Every time we needed something specific, we had to
                hack the core. Even when using it headless, it left dead code everywhere—WordPress was built as a
                monolith, not as a data source.
            </p>

            <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
                We then tried Sanity CMS and Strapi, which we loved for being truly headless. But there was a problem: <strong
                    class="text-white">Strapi was too heavy</strong
                > for a $4/month VPS. Both WordPress and Strapi devoured RAM and CPU.
            </p>

            <div class="p-6 bg-vayload-bg-card border-l-2 border-white/10 rounded-xl">
                <p class="text-neutral-400 italic">
                    "A friend asked for a store admin. She couldn't afford expensive hosting for her small business.
                    That's when we realized: <span class="text-orange-400 font-semibold"
                        >we needed something different</span
                    >."
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl bg-[#0a0a0c] border border-orange-500/20 shadow-2xl">
            <div class="text-center mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Vayload Difference</h3>
                <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">Optimized for small servers, scalable for millions</p>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-black/40 rounded-lg">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                        <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-red-500"></div>
                        <span class="text-neutral-300">WordPress</span>
                    </div>
                    <span class="text-red-400 text-sm">Heavy, monolithic</span>
                </div>

                <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-black/40 rounded-lg">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                        <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-yellow-500"></div>
                        <span class="text-neutral-300">Strapi</span>
                    </div>
                    <span class="text-yellow-400 text-sm">Resource intensive</span>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-orange-900/20 border border-orange-500/30 rounded-lg"
                >
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                        <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-orange-500"></div>
                        <span class="text-white font-semibold">Vayload</span>
                    </div>
                    <span class="text-orange-400 text-sm font-semibold">Lightweight & Fast</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="py-16 border-t border-white/5">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                Typed <span class="text-orange-500">EAV</span> Architecture
            </h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                We chose Entity-Attribute-Value with strict typing to enable concurrent multi-user editing without race
                conditions.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-vayload-bg-elevated border border-white/10">
                    <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                        <svg
                            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                            width="20"
                            height="20"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            stroke-linecap="round"
                            stroke-linejoin="round"
                            class="text-orange-500"
                        >
                            <ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"></ellipse>
                            <path d="M21 12c0 1.66-4 3-9 3s-9-1.34-9-3"></path>
                            <path d="M3 5v14c0 1.66 4 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3V5"></path>
                        </svg>
                        Why Not JSON or Flat Tables?
                    </h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-neutral-400">
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="text-red-400">✗</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong class="text-neutral-300">JSON Blobs:</strong> Race conditions when multiple users
                                edit (User A overwrites User B)</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="text-red-400">✗</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong class="text-neutral-300">Flat Tables:</strong> Require schema migrations for every
                                new field</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="text-green-400">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong class="text-white">Vayload EAV:</strong> Infinite fields without migrations + atomic
                                field-level updates</span
                            >
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-vayload-bg-elevated border border-white/10">
                    <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                        <svg
                            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                            width="20"
                            height="20"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            stroke-linecap="round"
                            stroke-linejoin="round"
                            class="text-green-500"
                        >
                            <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                        </svg>
                        Performance Mitigation
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-3">
                        EAV reads are inherently slower due to joins. We mitigate this via:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-300">
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <svg
                                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                                width="16"
                                height="16"
                                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                                fill="none"
                                stroke="currentColor"
                                stroke-width="2"
                                stroke-linecap="round"
                                stroke-linejoin="round"
                                class="text-green-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5"
                            >
                                <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                            </svg>
                            <span
                                ><strong class="text-white">Materialized Views:</strong> Flattens content for express reads</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <svg
                                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                                width="16"
                                height="16"
                                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                                fill="none"
                                stroke="currentColor"
                                stroke-width="2"
                                stroke-linecap="round"
                                stroke-linejoin="round"
                                class="text-green-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5"
                            >
                                <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                            </svg>
                            <span
                                ><strong class="text-white">Event-Driven Updates:</strong> Cache warms immediately on save</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <svg
                                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                                width="16"
                                height="16"
                                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                                fill="none"
                                stroke="currentColor"
                                stroke-width="2"
                                stroke-linecap="round"
                                stroke-linejoin="round"
                                class="text-green-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5"
                            >
                                <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                            </svg>
                            <span
                                ><strong class="text-white">Typed Indexing:</strong> We store <code
                                    class="text-orange-400 bg-white/10 px-1 rounded">Int</code
                                >, not just strings</span
                            >
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl bg-[#0a0a0c] border border-orange-500/20 shadow-2xl relative font-mono text-xs">
                <div
                    class="absolute -top-3 -right-3 bg-orange-600 text-white font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs shadow-lg"
                >
                    DATA LAYOUT
                </div>

                <div class="text-neutral-500 mb-2">// users_table (No locks here)</div>
                <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
                    <div class="flex gap-2 p-2 bg-black/40 border border-white/5 rounded opacity-50">
                        <span class="text-purple-400">Entity:101</span>
                        <span class="text-neutral-500">|</span>
                        <span class="text-neutral-400">Locked: False</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="text-neutral-500 mb-2">// attributes_table (Concurrent Writes)</div>
                <div class="space-y-2">
                    <div
                        class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 bg-black/40 border-l-2 border-green-500 rounded text-neutral-300"
                    >
                        <span class="text-purple-400">E:101</span>
                        <span class="text-blue-400">Attr:Stock</span>
                        <span class="text-yellow-400">Type:Int</span>
                        <span class="ml-auto text-green-400">Val:42</span>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 bg-black/40 border-l-2 border-blue-500 rounded text-neutral-300"
                    >
                        <span class="text-purple-400">E:101</span>
                        <span class="text-blue-400">Attr:Title</span>
                        <span class="text-yellow-400">Type:Str</span>
                        <span class="ml-auto text-green-400">"Product A"</span>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 bg-black/40 border-l-2 border-purple-500 rounded text-neutral-300"
                    >
                        <span class="text-purple-400">E:101</span>
                        <span class="text-blue-400">Attr:Price</span>
                        <span class="text-yellow-400">Type:Dec</span>
                        <span class="ml-auto text-green-400">Val:99.99</span>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 bg-black/40 border-l-2 border-orange-500 rounded text-neutral-300"
                    >
                        <span class="text-purple-400">E:101</span>
                        <span class="text-blue-400">Attr:Active</span>
                        <span class="text-yellow-400">Type:Bool</span>
                        <span class="ml-auto text-green-400">true</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-6 pt-4 border-t border-white/5 text-xs text-neutral-500">
                    <p>Each attribute is a separate row, enabling concurrent edits without conflicts.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
